'''Kabaitsuki Shrine''' (かばいづきじんじゃ) is a precinct shrine of Mizushi Shrine. It is a {{ill|lt=major shikinaisha|Q134917288|qid=Q134917288|1=Shikinai Taisha}}.

==== History ====
Its founding date is unknown. In the same {{ill|lt=Tsuzuki District|Q1154678|qid=Q1154678|1=Tsuzuki District, Kyoto}}, there is the shikinaisha {{ill|qid=Q595520|lt=Tsukuyomi Shrine (Kyotanabe)|Q54153263|qid=Q54153263|qid=Q595520|lt=Tsukuyomi Shrine|1=Tsukuyomi-no-Mikoto}}, and a relationship has been pointed out. It is also said that this shrine formerly stood in Osumi together with Tsukuyomi Shrine. However, due to flooding of the {{ill|lt=Kizu River (Kyoto)|Q3746236|qid=Q3746236|lt=Kizu River|1=Kizu River}}, the shrine buildings were washed away, and in {{ill|lt=1672|Q7614|qid=Q7614|1=1672}} ({{ill|lt=Kanbun|Q1146228|qid=Q1146228|1=Kanbun (era)}} 12) it was relocated into the precincts of Mizushi Shrine. Afterward it came under shared administration with Mizushi Shrine.

==== Divine rank ====
*{{ill|lt=Ten'an (Japan)|Q1075611|qid=Q1075611|lt=Ten'an|1=Ten'an}} 3 ({{ill|lt=859|Q23897|qid=Q23897|1=859}}) {{ill|lt=January 27|Q2284|qid=Q2284|1=January 27}}, promoted from Junior Fifth Rank Lower to Junior Fifth Rank Upper (''{{ill|lt=Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|Q1052981|qid=Q1052981|1=Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku}}'') - written as "Kabaitsuki no Kami"

